**Instructions:**

1.  Drag Troys_All_In_One.R into the files window on the bottom right of
    the screen Open the file, it will appear in the top-left of your
    screen

2.  Make sure you have the openintro and tidyverse packages downloaded

    -   To download these, use `install.packages(name)` in the console

        -   Wait for the first to finish downloading before starting the
            second

3.  Change line 10 through 18 as needed to load in your data Make sure
    to delete or edit the defaults

4.  To run the script, use `ctrl+A` to highlight everything in the
    script, and then press `ctrl+enter`
